Nowotny Says Not Helpful to Introduce Avalanche of New Measures

-- B y   S a n d r i n e   R a s t e l l o
-- 
2011-09-25T12:58:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/nowotny-says-not-helpful-to-introduce-avalanche-of-new-measures.html
European Central Bank Governing
Council member Ewald Nowotny said policy makers should implement
measures proposed in July first and that “introducing an
avalanche of new” proposals is “not helpful.” Nowotny was
speaking in  Washington  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sandrine Rastello in Washington at 
 srastello@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gabi Thesing at 
 gthesing@bloomberg.net  